todo.md

# Server-generated experiment outputs. These are reproducible from the
# checkpoint + test split via experiments/bias_pruning/scripts/evaluate_subgroup_wer.py,
# so keeping them out of git avoids merge conflicts when a server run
# overwrites the laptop's copies. The directories themselves are kept via
# .gitkeep so `compare_conditions.py` has somewhere to drop new outputs.
experiments/bias_pruning/results/per_utterance/*.csv
experiments/bias_pruning/results/per_seed_wer/*.csv
!experiments/bias_pruning/results/per_utterance/.gitkeep
!experiments/bias_pruning/results/per_seed_wer/.gitkeep

# Comparison-level outputs ARE committed (final_comparison.csv,
# disparity_metrics.csv, paired_bootstrap.csv, comparison_plot.png) —
# those are the human-readable results referenced in summary.md.
# Restricted-license datasets (Fair-Speech etc.) must never have their
# transcripts redistributed. The general per_utterance/*.csv rule above
# already blocks them.